15#ifndef DNS_RDATASLAB_H
16#define DNS_RDATASLAB_H 1
17
18/*! \file dns/rdataslab.h
19 * \brief
20 * Implements storage of rdatasets into slabs of memory.
21 *
22 * MP:
23 *\li Clients of this module must impose any required synchronization.
24 *
25 * Reliability:
26 *\li This module deals with low-level byte streams. Errors in any of
27 * the functions are likely to crash the server or corrupt memory.
28 *
29 *\li If the caller passes invalid memory references, these functions are
30 * likely to crash the server or corrupt memory.
31 *
32 * Resources:
33 *\li None.
34 *
35 * Security:
36 *\li None.
37 *
38 * Standards:
39 *\li None.
40 */
41
42/***
43 *** Imports
44 ***/
45
46#include <stdbool.h>
47
48#include <isc/lang.h>
49
50#include <dns/types.h>
51
52ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
53
54#define DNS_RDATASLAB_FORCE 0x1
55#define DNS_RDATASLAB_EXACT 0x2
56
57#define DNS_RDATASLAB_OFFLINE 0x01 /* RRSIG is for offline DNSKEY */
58#define DNS_RDATASLAB_WARNMASK 0x0E /*%< RRSIG(DNSKEY) expired
59 * warnings number mask. */
60#define DNS_RDATASLAB_WARNSHIFT 1 /*%< How many bits to shift to find
61 * remaining expired warning number. */
62
63
64/***
65 *** Functions
66 ***/
67
68isc_result_t
69dns_rdataslab_fromrdataset(dns_rdataset_t *rdataset, isc_mem_t *mctx,
70 isc_region_t *region, unsigned int reservelen);
71/*%<
72 * Slabify a rdataset. The slab area will be allocated and returned
73 * in 'region'.
74 *
75 * Requires:
76 *\li 'rdataset' is valid.
77 *
78 * Ensures:
79 *\li 'region' will have base pointing to the start of allocated memory,
80 * with the slabified region beginning at region->base + reservelen.
81 * region->length contains the total length allocated.
82 *
83 * Returns:
84 *\li ISC_R_SUCCESS - successful completion
85 *\li ISC_R_NOMEMORY - no memory.
86 *\li XXX others
87 */
88
89unsigned int
90dns_rdataslab_size(unsigned char *slab, unsigned int reservelen);
91/*%<
92 * Return the total size of an rdataslab.
93 *
94 * Requires:
95 *\li 'slab' points to a slab.
96 *
97 * Returns:
98 *\li The number of bytes in the slab, including the reservelen.
99 */
100
101unsigned int
102dns_rdataslab_count(unsigned char *slab, unsigned int reservelen);
103/*%<
104 * Return the number of records in the rdataslab
105 *
106 * Requires:
107 *\li 'slab' points to a slab.
108 *
109 * Returns:
110 *\li The number of records in the slab.
111 */
112
113isc_result_t
114dns_rdataslab_merge(unsigned char *oslab, unsigned char *nslab,
115 unsigned int reservelen, isc_mem_t *mctx,
116 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass, dns_rdatatype_t type,
117 unsigned int flags, unsigned char **tslabp);
118/*%<
119 * Merge 'oslab' and 'nslab'.
120 */
121
122isc_result_t
123dns_rdataslab_subtract(unsigned char *mslab, unsigned char *sslab,
124 unsigned int reservelen, isc_mem_t *mctx,
125 dns_rdataclass_t rdclass, dns_rdatatype_t type,
126 unsigned int flags, unsigned char **tslabp);
127/*%<
128 * Subtract 'sslab' from 'mslab'. If 'exact' is true then all elements
129 * of 'sslab' must exist in 'mslab'.
130 *
131 * XXX
132 * valid flags are DNS_RDATASLAB_EXACT
133 */
134
135bool
136dns_rdataslab_equal(unsigned char *slab1, unsigned char *slab2,
137 unsigned int reservelen);
138/*%<
139 * Compare two rdataslabs for equality. This does _not_ do a full
140 * DNSSEC comparison.
141 *
142 * Requires:
143 *\li 'slab1' and 'slab2' point to slabs.
144 *
145 * Returns:
146 *\li true if the slabs are equal, false otherwise.
147 */
148bool
149dns_rdataslab_equalx(unsigned char *slab1, unsigned char *slab2,
150 unsigned int reservelen, dns_rdataclass_t rdclass,
151 dns_rdatatype_t type);
152/*%<
153 * Compare two rdataslabs for DNSSEC equality.
154 *
155 * Requires:
156 *\li 'slab1' and 'slab2' point to slabs.
157 *
158 * Returns:
159 *\li true if the slabs are equal, #false otherwise.
160 */
161
162ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS
163
164#endif /* DNS_RDATASLAB_H */
